data.title: Private Equity
data.meta_description: WSJ Pro Private Equity is a premium membership product for elite practitioners, powered by The Wall Street Journal’s peerless reporting and Dow Jones’ unrivaled data.
data.text:
Mark Burgett pleaded guilty to a domestic violence charge and resigned from the food-focused firm, raising questions about its future.

The provider of heating, ventilation and air conditioning equipment said it expects to complete the sale to the private-equity firm by the end of the year.

A KKR-led consortium has started the process of selling its entire stake in the largest private hospital in the Philippines in a deal that could value the business at around $3.0 billion, people familiar with the process said.
